---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import IllustrationMaterial from '../components/IllustrationMaterial.astro';
import IllustrationLayers from '../components/IllustrationLayers.astro';
import IllustrationCliff from '../components/IllustrationCliff.astro';
import IllustrationReproduce from '../components/IllustrationReproduce.astro';
---

<Base title="Augmented Engineering — Patterns for working with AI agents">
  <header class="hero">
    <h1>Your AI agent keeps making the same mistakes.</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">It sounds confident but gets the numbers wrong. It ignores your docs. It forgets what you told it yesterday. These aren't bugs — they're material properties you can design around.</p>
    <p class="subtitle">Four patterns, each one something you can try Monday morning.</p>
  </header>

  <section id="patterns" class="patterns-section">
    <h2>The Patterns</h2>

    <div class="pattern-grid">
      <a href="/patterns/learn-the-material" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-illustration">
          <IllustrationMaterial />
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-text">
          <h3>1. Learn the Material</h3>
          <p class="pattern-problem">Your LLM says "demonstrates" when the evidence only "suggests." It scores good work low and bad work high.</p>
          <p class="pattern-fix">These are material properties — design around them instead of fighting them. Know which ones are permanent and which are being fixed.</p>
          <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/patterns/layer-your-verification" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-illustration">
          <IllustrationLayers />
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-text">
          <h3>2. Layer Your Verification</h3>
          <p class="pattern-problem">You reviewed the AI's output and it looked fine. Then a colleague found three errors in the first page.</p>
          <p class="pattern-fix">Run multiple verification passes — each one catches what the others miss. The second pass costs minutes and regularly finds what the first one didn't.</p>
          <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/patterns/context-is-architecture" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-illustration">
          <IllustrationCliff />
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-text">
          <h3>3. Context Is Architecture</h3>
          <p class="pattern-problem">You wrote great docs but your agent ignores them. You explained the same thing three sessions in a row.</p>
          <p class="pattern-fix">There's a hard cliff between what agents load automatically and what's invisible. Task-triggered pointers cross it. Descriptive labels don't.</p>
          <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/patterns/reproduce-dont-assess" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-illustration">
          <IllustrationReproduce />
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-text">
          <h3>4. Reproduce, Don't Assess</h3>
          <p class="pattern-problem">You asked the AI to check your equations and it said they looked fine. They weren't.</p>
          <p class="pattern-fix">Don't ask "is this right?" Ask "compute this from scratch and compare." Assessment found 0 errors in 68 equations. Reproduction found 3.</p>
          <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="quick-ref" class="quickref-section">
    <h2>Quick Reference</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">When you hit one of these situations, reach for the corresponding pattern.</p>

    <table class="quickref-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Situation</th><th>Pattern</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>LLM gave me a number</td><td><a href="/patterns/reproduce-dont-assess">Reproduce it</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>LLM scored or rated something</td><td><a href="/patterns/learn-the-material">Don't trust it — separate scoring</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>LLM sounds very confident</td><td><a href="/patterns/learn-the-material">Check the evidence tier</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Agent isn't using my docs</td><td><a href="/patterns/context-is-architecture">Check if it's below the cliff</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>One review pass found nothing</td><td><a href="/patterns/layer-your-verification">Run another layer</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Agent keeps forgetting decisions</td><td><a href="/patterns/context-is-architecture">Use task-triggered pointers</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>AI review says "looks good"</td><td><a href="/patterns/reproduce-dont-assess">Compute, don't assess</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Choosing between approaches</td><td><a href="/patterns/layer-your-verification">Have a second agent review the first</a></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="about-section">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="about-content">
      <p>Four patterns from nine real projects (embedded hardware, physics simulation, academic writing, news curation, and more) built over 2025-2026. One engineer's practice — not a validated framework. Honest about limitations, survivorship bias, and sample size.</p>
      <p>The patterns are worth trying. The framing is worth debating.</p>
      <div class="about-cta">
        <p><a href="https://github.com/ducroq/augmented-engineering">Source, evidence, and case studies on GitHub</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    color: var(--ink-light);
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Pattern cards */
  .pattern-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-card {
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 2px solid var(--ink-faint);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .pattern-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--ink);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .pattern-illustration {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 200px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .pattern-illustration :global(.illustration) {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 200px;
  }

  .pattern-text {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.3rem 0;
  }

  .pattern-text h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .pattern-problem {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .pattern-fix {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .read-more {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--blue-pencil);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Quick reference */
  .quickref-section {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .quickref-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .quickref-table th,
  .quickref-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .quickref-table th {
    font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .quickref-table td {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .quickref-table td:first-child {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .quickref-table td:last-child {
    color: var(--ink-light);
  }

  .quickref-table a {
    color: var(--blue-pencil);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .quickref-table a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-style: wavy;
  }

  /* About */
  .about-section {
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .about-cta {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.3rem;
    background: var(--paper-dark);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .about-cta p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pattern-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
  }
</style>
